# Trustscrow Assessment Test

This project is a REST API of an Event Management System explaining; explaining how the API manages the Event Category resources.

The implementation of the REST API is done using:

- Typescript
- Express JS
- Sequelize
- Postgres SQL

## Setting up the Project

`Clone the project`
`Install the node modules - npm install`
`Configure your database credentials on (config.ts)`

## Run APP

`npm run dev or yarn dev`

## Test APP

`npm run test or yarn test`

## API Reference

#### Get all categories

```http
  GET /
```

#### Get a single category

```http
  GET /:id
```

#### Add New Category

```http
  POST /
```

| Parameter   | Type      | Description  |
| :---------- | :-------- | :----------- |
| `name`      | `string`  | **Required** |
| `parent_id` | `integer` | **Optional** |

#### Update item

```http
  PATCH /:id
```

| Parameter   | Type     | Description  |
| :---------- | :------- | :----------- |
| `name`      | `string` | **Required** |
| `parent_id` | `string` | **Optional** |

#### Delete category

```http
  DELETE /:id
```

